attributes.background:
This will allow any registered user to directly contribute to the formulation of government policy and have that contribution considered, discussed and debated by any other member of the public and ultimately by the government itself.

This would:

a) Be a huge step forward in the democratic transparency and accountability of policy making;

b) Massively increase public engagement in and ownership of the policy making process;

c) Significantly increase the pool of knowledge, experience, ideas and criticism that policy making is exposed to, giving a much better end product.
